- clear makes float element outer container to be as tall as float elements inside it.
So always addded a div at end of all divs with class="clear-fix"

- Margin -> go with em , padding and top/left/right -> go with px
- when float -> width comes in %


Header:
-------
header
section
nav
footer



Global layout rules:
--------------------

body{
    margin:0px;
    padding:0px;
}

header a.logo{
    display:block;
    position:absolute;
    background-position:0px 0px;
    background-repeat:no-repeat;
}

header{
    height:225px;
    background:url(.../images/banner_large.jpg) no-repeat right 0px;

}


CSS:
----
background: #5d357d url(../images/background_gradient.jpg) repeat-x 0px 0px;
background:url(.../images/banner_large.jpg) no-repeat right center;
.page{  //This is a div container after body
    max-width:980px;
    margin: 0px auto 0px auto; //Divide the gap equally between left and right
    position:relative;
}

nav{
    width:100%;
    display:block;
    position:absolute; //This is relative to the page
    top:225px;
}

using ems:

body{
    font-size:14px;
}


h1{
    margin:0em 0em .75em 0em;
}

p{
    line-height:1.4em;
    margin:0em 0em .75em 0em;
}

padding -> put in px
margin and font size put in em

.promo p{ //element parent has class
}

.promo.test{ //Two classes added side by side

}

a.cta{ //element + class on that element

}

CSS:
----
.promo{
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    text-transform:uppercase
}

.clear-fix{
    clear:both;
    line-height:1px;
}



Media queries:
--------------
float:none;
width:auto;

For small screen devices:
-------------------------
- Put navigation as static



